race.comment: SEQUEL (9) was tried at Group level and then placed at Warwick Farm at her only start last preparation. Resumed at Newcastle 13 days ago and looked a run short. She's been switched north by the Waller yard and this looks winnable with the extra fitness. SHORTCUT (10) resumes and two back was narrowly beaten her in an Open 2 on debut. Brings two trial placings and will be naturally improved. Draws awkwardly but she can feature with average luck. MOON JEWEL (6) resumes and two starts back was tried stakes level. Owns two trial wins and gets in light with the 3kg claim. She will get every chance and the betting will be key. CARAMELFUDGESUNDAE (5) found more like her best placing at the Sunshine Coast second-up and Ben Thompson rides today. She went well here prior to the spell and goes in at a price.
